The paper deals with the construction of Toeplitz compressed sensing matrices for linear system identification, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Systems and Control (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper also discusses the properties of the constructed sequences, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as well.
